<h2>Key points</h2>
<ul>
<li>Energy boosting is when you increase the amount of calories in the food your child eats so that they can gain weight and have more energy.</li>
<li>To increase the amount of calories your child is getting only eat during regular meals and snacks, offer them foods that are highest in calories first and lowest in calories last, and add extra calories to their foods.</li>
</ul>
